#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.83"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.83:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.83:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.83:0.3"
msgid "83. Ānandasutta"
msgstr "83. With Ānanda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.105"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.83:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.83:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā ānando bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Ānanda addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn22.83:1.3"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn22.83:1.4"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn22.83:1.5"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:"
msgstr "Ānanda said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: mantāṇiputto → mantāniputto (bj, pts1, mr) | mantānīputto (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn22.83:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Puṇṇo nāma, āvuso, āyasmā mantāṇiputto amhākaṃ navakānaṃ sataṃ bahūpakāro "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, the venerable named Puṇṇa Mantāniputta was very helpful to me "
"when I was just ordained."

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.2"
msgid "So amhe iminā ovādena ovadati:"
msgstr "He gave me this advice:"

# Take care of the double nested quotes.
msgctxt "sn22.83:2.3"
msgid "‘upādāya, āvuso ānanda, asmīti hoti, no anupādāya."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Ānanda, the notion “I am” occurs because of grasping, not by not "
"grasping."

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.4"
msgid "Kiñca upādāya asmīti hoti, no anupādāya?"
msgstr "Grasping what?"

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.5"
msgid "Rūpaṃ upādāya asmīti hoti, no anupādāya."
msgstr "The notion “I am” occurs because of grasping form,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.6"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "feeling,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.7"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.8"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:2.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ upādāya asmīti hoti, no anupādāya."
msgstr "and consciousness, not by not grasping."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.83:3.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso ānanda, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko "
"ādāse vā parisuddhe pariyodāte acche vā udakapatte sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ "
"paccavekkhamāno upādāya passeyya, no anupādāya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of "
"adornments, and they check their own reflection in a clean bright mirror or "
"a clear bowl of water. They’d look because of grasping, not by not grasping."

msgctxt "sn22.83:3.2"
msgid "evameva kho, āvuso ānanda, rūpaṃ upādāya asmīti hoti, no anupādāya."
msgstr "In the same way, the notion “I am” occurs because of grasping form,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:3.3"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "feeling,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:3.4"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:3.5"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices,"

msgctxt "sn22.83:3.6"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ upādāya asmīti hoti, no anupādāya."
msgstr "and consciousness, not by not grasping."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.106"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.83:4.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso ānanda, "
msgstr "What do you think, Reverend Ānanda? "

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā’ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?’"

# Note here the extreme equality in terms of address: even a newly ordained monk speaks like this to their teacher.
msgctxt "sn22.83:4.3"
msgid "‘Aniccaṃ, āvuso’."
msgstr "‘Impermanent, reverend.’"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.4"
msgid "‘Vedanā …"
msgstr "‘Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.5"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.6"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā’ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?’"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.8"
msgid "‘Aniccaṃ, āvuso’ … pe …."
msgstr "‘Impermanent, reverend.’ …"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.9"
msgid "Tasmātiha … pe …"
msgstr "‘So you should truly see …"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.10"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.11"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātīti."
msgstr "They understand: “… there is no return to any state of existence.”’"

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.12"
msgid ""
"Puṇṇo nāma, āvuso, āyasmā mantāṇiputto amhākaṃ navakānaṃ sataṃ bahūpakāro "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"Reverends, the venerable named Puṇṇa Mantāniputta was very helpful to me "
"when I was just ordained."

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.13"
msgid "So amhe iminā ovādena ovadati."
msgstr "He gave me this advice."

msgctxt "sn22.83:4.14"
msgid ""
"Idañca pana me āyasmato puṇṇassa mantāṇiputtassa dhammadesanaṃ sutvā dhammo "
"abhisamito”ti."
msgstr ""
"And now that I’ve heard this teaching from Venerable Puṇṇa Mantāniputta, I’"
"ve comprehended the teaching.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.83:4.15"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
